For Garry Monk, the frustration was obvious. Aside from the goal they conceded, this was a game Swansea largely dominated.

Bafetimbi Gomis was denied after going clean through at the end of a delightful six-man, first-half move and Ki also had a goal disallowed. Almost immediately, Defoe took possession just inside Swansea's half and easily beat Federico Fernandez before finishing from 20 yards.

Ki levelled after the break, but Monk said: 'It was frustrating. We had enough good chances to take the points. The only shot they had was the goal - we gave Defoe too much space.'

On Ki's disallowed goal, Monk added: 'I was told his hairline was offside, although I am not sure that is part of the rules. I will have to tell Ki to cut his hair.'  

